    <abstract>
      <t>This draft describes operational procedures aimed at reducing the amount of traffic lost during planned maintenances of routers or links, involving the shutdown of BGP peering sessions. It defines a well-known BGP community, called g-shut, to signal the graceful shutdown of paths to other Autonomous Systems.</t>
